Installing php5-override extension
    __________________________________________________________________

    * General Installation Considerations
    * Compiling the extension on Linux or Unix systems
    * Installation
    * Problems?
    __________________________________________________________________


General Installation Considerations

    Prerequisite knowledge and software for compiling :
        * Basic Unix skills (being able to operate "make" and a C compiler)
        * An ANSI C compiler

    When building directly from Git sources you might also need :
        * autoconf: 2.13+ (for PHP < 5.4.0), 2.59+ (for PHP >= 5.4.0)
        * automake: 1.4+
        * libtool: 1.4.x+ (except 1.4.2)
        * flex: Version 2.5.4 (for PHP <= 5.2)
        * bison: Version 1.28 (preferred), 1.35, or 1.75
        * phpize

    Debian GNU/Linux installation notes:
        * php5-dev package is recommended in order to compile the php5-override extension

    Compatibility:
        * php5-override is compatible with all versions of PHP5
     __________________________________________________________________

Compiling on Linux or Unix systems

1.  cd src
2.  phpize
3.  ./configure
4.  make
5.  make install

     __________________________________________________________________

Installation

     The override extension is not enabled by default, so the override.so librarie must be enabled inside of your php.ini.

     __________________________________________________________________

Problems?

    You should report bugs or installation problems at:
    https://github.com/OlympeNetwork/php5-override/issues/new
    or by mail: support at anotherservice.com
